The paper deals with decoding of LDPC codes over the BSC, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves searching for a set of flips, which can be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem (cs.DS). The LP decoder is a linear programming problem, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the properties of the LDPC code, which is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper proposes an efficient algorithm for generating instantons, which can be seen as a problem in computational complexity (cs.SI).
